{"entryType":"UniProtKB reviewed (Swiss-Prot)","primaryAccession":"Q12WS1","uniProtkbId":"DADD_METBU","entryAudit":{"firstPublicDate":"2007-12-04","lastAnnotationUpdateDate":"2026-01-28","lastSequenceUpdateDate":"2006-08-22","entryVersion":99,"sequenceVersion":1},"annotationScore":4.0,"organism":{"scientificName":"Methanococcoides burtonii (strain DSM 6242 / NBRC 107633 / OCM 468 / ACE-M)","taxonId":259564,"lineage":["Archaea","Methanobacteriati","Methanobacteriota","Stenosarchaea group","Methanomicrobia","Methanosarcinales","Methanosarcinaceae","Methanococcoides"]},"proteinExistence":"3: Inferred from homology","proteinDescription":{"recommendedName":{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"5'-deoxyadenosine deaminase"},"shortNames":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"5'-dA deaminase"}],"ecNumbers":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"3.5.4.41"}]},"alternativeNames":[{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"5'-methylthioadenosine deaminase"},"shortNames":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"MTA deaminase"}],"ecNumbers":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"3.5.4.31"}]},{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"Adenosine deaminase"},"ecNumbers":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"3.5.4.4"}]},{"fullName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"S-adenosylhomocysteine deaminase"},"shortNames":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"SAH deaminase"}],"ecNumbers":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"3.5.4.28"}]}]},"genes":[{"geneName":{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"dadD"},"orderedLocusNames":[{"value":"Mbur_1182"}]}],"comments":[{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"Catalyzes the deamination of three SAM-derived enzymatic products, namely 5'-deoxyadenosine, S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine, and 5'-methylthioadenosine, to produce the inosine analogs. Can also deaminate adenosine. The preferred substrate for this enzyme is 5'-deoxyadenosine, but all these substrates are efficiently deaminated. Likely functions in a S-adenosyl-L-methionine (SAM) recycling pathway from S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine (SAH) produced from SAM-dependent methylation reactions. May also be involved in the recycling of 5'-deoxyadenosine, whereupon the 5'-deoxyribose moiety of 5'-deoxyinosine is further metabolized to deoxyhexoses used for the biosynthesis of aromatic amino acids in methanogens"}],"commentType":"FUNCTION"},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"5'-deoxyadenosine + H2O + H(+) = 5'-deoxyinosine + NH4(+)","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:42892"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15377"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:17319"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:28938"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:82775"}],"ecNumber":"3.5.4.41","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:42893"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]}]},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H2O + H(+) = S-inosyl-L-homocysteine + NH4(+)","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:20716"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15377"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:28938"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:57856"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:57985"}],"ecNumber":"3.5.4.28","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:20717"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]}]},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"S-methyl-5'-thioadenosine + H2O + H(+) = S-methyl-5'-thioinosine + NH4(+)","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:25025"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15377"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:17509"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:28938"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:48595"}],"ecNumber":"3.5.4.31","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:25026"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]}]},{"commentType":"CATALYTIC ACTIVITY","reaction":{"name":"adenosine + H2O + H(+) = inosine + NH4(+)","reactionCrossReferences":[{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:24408"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15377"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:15378"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:16335"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:17596"},{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:28938"}],"ecNumber":"3.5.4.4","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]},"physiologicalReactions":[{"directionType":"left-to-right","reactionCrossReference":{"database":"Rhea","id":"RHEA:24409"},"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}]}]},{"commentType":"COFACTOR","cofactors":[{"name":"Zn(2+)","evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"cofactorCrossReference":{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:29105"}}],"note":{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"Binds 1 zinc ion per subunit."}]}},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"Amino-acid biosynthesis; S-adenosyl-L-methionine biosynthesis"}],"commentType":"PATHWAY"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"Homotetramer"}],"commentType":"SUBUNIT"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"SAH is a product of SAM methyltransferases and is known to be a feedback inhibitor of these enzymes. As a result of this inhibition, organisms have evolved efficient enzymes to metabolize SAH via different pathways. The pathway found in methanogens differs from the canonical pathway, it uses the deamination of S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine to form S-inosyl-L-homocysteine for the regeneration of SAM from S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine. 5'-deoxyadenosine is a radical SAM enzyme reaction product which strongly inhibits radical SAM enzymes. A pathway for removing this product must be present in methanogens where the MTA/SAH nucleosidase which normally metabolizes this compound is absent"}],"commentType":"MISCELLANEOUS"},{"texts":[{"evidences":[{"evidenceCode":"ECO:0000255","source":"HAMAP-Rule","id":"MF_01281"}],"value":"Belongs to the metallo-dependent hydrolases superfamily. MTA/SAH deaminase family"}],"commentType":"SIMILARITY"}],"features":[{"type":"Chain","location":{"start":{"value":1,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":434,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"5'-deoxyadenosine deaminase","featureId":"PRO_0000312470"},{"type":"Binding site","location":{"start":{"value":63,"modifier":"EXACT"},"end":{"value":63,"modifier":"EXACT"}},"description":"","featureCrossReferences":[{"database":"ChEBI","id":"CHEBI:29105"}],"ev